
[1]supplication

   SUPPLICA'TION, n. [L. supplicatio.]

   1. Entreaty; humble and earnest prayer in worship. In all our
   supplications to the Father of mercies, let us remember a world lying
   in ignorance and wickedness.

   2. Petition; earnest request.

   3. In Roman antiquity, a religious solemnity observed in consequence of
   some military success. It consisted in sacrifices, feasting, offering
   thanks, and praying for a continuance of success.
